Principal Deputy National Security Advisor Jon Finer led a U.S. delegation to New Delhi for a review of the U.S-India Initiative on Critical and Emerging Technology (iCET). The iCET is an important aspect of the U.S.-India partnership, which focuses on strategic security and technology cooperation. During the visit, Mr. Finer held discussions with Indian officials, including Deputy National Security Advisor Vikram Misri, Minister of External Affairs S. Jaishankar, National Security Advisor Ajit Doval, and Foreign Secretary Vinay Kwatra. The discussions aimed to enhance coordination and policy alignment across the Indo-Pacific, including the Indian Ocean region. Topics covered included the recent attacks on commercial vessels in the Red Sea, the importance of safeguarding freedom of commercial navigation, plans for a post-conflict Gaza, and efforts towards a two-state solution. Mr. Finer also acknowledged India's establishment of a Committee of Enquiry to investigate lethal plotting in the United States and stressed the importance of holding accountable those responsible.